## Entry Point Flow

### index.html

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Zoo Builder</title>
  <style>
    * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
    body {
      background: #0d0d1a;
      display: flex;
      justify-content: center;
      align-items: center;
      height: 100vh;
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    canvas {
      image-rendering: pixelated;
      image-rendering: crisp-edges;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <canvas id="game" width="1280" height="720" aria-label="Zoo Builder game canvas">
    Zoo Builder: A zoo management simulation game. Use mouse to interact and keyboard for shortcuts.
  </canvas>
  <script type="module" src="/src/main.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

### src/main.js

```js
import { createGameState } from './state.js';
import { startGameLoop } from './game_loop.js';
import { setupInput } from './input.js';
import { initAudio } from './audio.js';
import { loadSaveSlots } from './save_system.js';

const canvas = document.getElementById('game');
const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');

// Disable image smoothing for pixel-art crispness
ctx.imageSmoothingEnabled = false;

const state = createGameState();
const saveSlots = loadSaveSlots();

setupInput(canvas, state);
initAudio();
startGameLoop(ctx, state);
```

## Error Handling Strategy

1. **Graceful degradation:** If audio context fails to initialize (e.g., autoplay policy), the game runs silently. Audio functions become no-ops.
2. **Save corruption:** `deserializeState` wraps parsing in try/catch. If a save slot contains invalid JSON or a version mismatch that cannot be migrated, the slot is marked as corrupted and the player is warned. The game does not crash.
3. **Frame budget overrun:** If a single update takes > 50ms (3x the budget), the delta accumulator is clamped to prevent a "spiral of death" where the simulation tries to catch up and falls further behind.
4. **Missing assets:** All rendering uses procedural drawing (colored rectangles, circles, lines). There are no external image assets that can fail to load. If a future version adds sprite sheets, the renderer falls back to procedural shapes on load error.
5. **Input edge cases:** All coordinate translations clamp to map bounds. Clicking outside the map grid is a no-op. Double-click does not trigger double-actions.

## Performance Budget

| Metric | Target | Measurement |
|--------|--------|-------------|
| Frame time | < 16ms | `performance.now()` delta in game loop |
| Update phase | < 8ms | Profile in devtools |
| Render phase | < 8ms | Profile in devtools |
| Memory (heap) | < 100MB | Chrome DevTools memory panel |
| JS bundle (gzip) | < 50KB | Vite build output |
| Initial load | < 2s | Lighthouse on 3G throttle |

